        <section eId="sec_12_476b">
          <num>12-476b</num>
          <heading>Identification of vehicles transporting fuel. Penalty for failure to comply</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 12-476b. Identification of vehicles transporting fuel. Penalty for failure to comply.All vehicles used in transporting fuel shall be identified by having the name or trade name of the true owner or the lessee thereof printed in plain view on both sides of the vehicle in prominent and legible letters not less than one and one-half inches in height. Any person who violates any provision of this section shall be fined five hundred dollars for each offense.
